{
  "stem": "14897.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he said, you know, this is kind of risky.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Who ever heard of a Jew of his own volition showing up at the Gestapo?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father said, you know, because it is so rare, it might work.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he went-- this Pole-- went to speak to he superior, the Gestapo officer, who was so intrigued by it, he said, I will see these people.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Do you know the names of either the Pole or the Gestapo officer?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I don't know the names.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I've never met them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I just know the story from my parents.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the, the interview took place, of course, at the office of the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Gestapo officer, it turned out, was a man-- I don't know, in his 50s, 40s, something like that-- was also involved in the First World War.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this was kind of a point that he and my father had in common, their hatred of Russia.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they had a conversation, which was apparently rather amicable.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And at the end of it, he gave my father and my mother a pass to go to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my mother was so unrealistic that when she came-- when they came back, she looked at this pass.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she said, it doesn't say 'with luggage.' So my father went back, and it was added, [GERMAN], you know, with luggage.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So now we have the pass.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We are still afraid to get on a train because the first German soldier can take the pass, and tear it, and do anything that he wants.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my father had friends with whom he had been in prison, local people who ran a tavern, not Jewish people, who were very fond of my father.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
